<ext_description linkend="Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_with_uncertainty">
A <b>Representation_with_uncertainty</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation"/> that specifies uncertainty with
respect to the elements of representation that it collects. The uncertainty is specified by instances of
<express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation.context_of_items"/>, and applies to all elements of representation that are
expressed in the same measures.
<example>In an domain is acoustical engineering, there
could be an uncertainty of 1 decibel in the values that represent the relative loudness of sounds.
</example>
If uncertainties are specified more than once, the following precedence rules shall apply:
<ul>
<li>The uncertainty specified for an individual element of representation shall have precedence over the
uncertainty specified by any <express_ref linkend="representation_with_uncertainty:arm:Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_with_uncertainty"/> in which the item participates;
</li>
<li>The uncertainty specified by an <express_ref linkend="representation_with_uncertainty:arm:Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_with_uncertainty"/> shall have precedence over
the uncertainty specified by any <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Numerical_representation_context"/> in which the representation
participates.
</li>
</ul>
<note number="1">This entity may be combined with the entity <express_ref linkend="external_model:arm:External_model_arm.External_geometric_model"/> in an instance, 
to represent the accuracies that apply to the external geometry.</note>
<note number="2">This entity enables to group a subset of the items of a <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation"/>, that conform to particular accuracies.
In such a case, the <express_ref linkend="representation_with_uncertainty:arm:Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_with_uncertainty"/> will share the same <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation.context_of_items"/> as the other Representation, stating that their items are founded in a unique context, and have specific uncertainty measures.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Representation_with_uncertainty_arm  Entity: Representation_with_uncertainty  Attribute: uncertainty 
   <express_ref linkend="representation_with_uncertainty:arm:Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_with_uncertainty.uncertainty"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_with_uncertainty.uncertainty">
the set of instances of <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation.context_of_items"/> that apply to instances of
<express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_item"/> in the <express_ref linkend="representation_with_uncertainty:arm:Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_with_uncertainty"/>.
<p>The set shall not contain instances of <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation.context_of_items"/> that have the same name.</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Representation_with_uncertainty_arm  Entity: Representation_item_with_uncertainty  
   <express_ref linkend="representation_with_uncertainty:arm:Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_item_with_uncertainty"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_item_with_uncertainty">
A <b>Representation_item_with_uncertainty</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_item"/> for which particular uncertainties apply onto the measures that characterize it.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Representation_with_uncertainty_arm  Entity: Representation_item_with_uncertainty  Attribute: uncertainty 
   <express_ref linkend="representation_with_uncertainty:arm:Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_item_with_uncertainty.uncertainty"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Representation_item_with_uncertainty.uncertainty">
the set of instances of <express_ref linkend="representation_with_uncertainty:arm:Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Uncertainty_value"/> that apply to the measures that characterize the representation item.
<p>The set shall not contain instances of <express_ref linkend="representation_with_uncertainty:arm:Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Uncertainty_value"/> that have the same name.</p>
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Uncertainty_value">
An <b>Uncertainty_value</b> is the named measure value that defines an uncertainty. 
<p>The uncertainty applies to any measure for which it is relevant.
</p>
<example>An uncertainty named 'distance accuracy' would be relevant for geometric entities.</example>
<p>The uncertainty value is specified unitless. 
However, when applied to a measure with unit, this unit applies to the uncertainty value.</p>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Uncertainty_value.name">
the text that specifies the kind of uncertainty.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Uncertainty_value.uncertainty">
the real value of the uncertainty.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Uncertainty_value.description">
a text that provides further information about the <express_ref linkend="representation_with_uncertainty:arm:Representation_with_uncertainty_arm.Uncertainty_value"/>. The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>

